title: Okay, hear me out
body:
The big problem with Andi’s ‘dating storylines’ and her 'relationships’ is, that we get to see what’s messed up with it but nobody explicitly tells the (young) viewers that it is, in fact, not… healthy.
Like… I’m missing a clear message here: 'What we show you here is not okay!’. The average viewer on tumblr may know this, but can we expect children who watch the show to know this, too? (I mean, for instance, look at Tuffys and the whole nine-year-old Jandi squad…)
I sometimes have the feeling that none of the adults on the show actually give ‘good advice’ to Andi (on the topic of relationships). Everybody wants to see her in relationships and nothing on the show critisizes it (except for Buffy that one time - then they changed that in favor of Jandi).
I’m talking about the whole ‘We shouldn’t talk or text anymore, Walker” stuff and the whole jealousy thing with Jonah, inviting Natalie, and his and Andi’s reactions in general. That’s honestly kind of messed up? And it isn’t… like… addressed in any second of the show? None?
If Bex and Bowie wouldn’t constantly push Andi into this relationship… that would be a really good start?

For the record, this isn’t an anti-Jonah or anti-Andi post. I love them both very much and I don’t think there is any intent of harm in their actions. But… can this be like addressed on the show? For at least one (1) scene or something?
